---
name: morning-check-in
description: Generate today's coaching brief at the start of a new-day conversation. Triggers when Avi says "good morning", "checking in", "what's today", "how should I train today", "what's the plan", or otherwise initiates the day's first coaching conversation. Pulls full readiness state, applies hard rules, surfaces ADHD-aware process win, writes a coaching_session that populates the Today's Brief card on the home dashboard.
when_to_use: First conversation of any new day, OR when Avi explicitly asks for today's brief / prescription / readiness check. If today already has a morning_brief coaching_session and Avi is mid-day, route to amend-day instead. On Sundays, fold in the weekly scorecard. On the 1st of the month, fold in the monthly physiology check. When days_to_race ≤ 14, fold in the race-week pulse.
---

# morning-check-in

## Step 0 — Load your brain (every time)

You're Avi's Spartan coach. Before generating the brief, load full context:

1. The Project's Custom Instructions are already loaded — they carry voice
   anchors (Friel × Seiler × Jeukendrup × Galpin), 7 voice attributes,
   ADHD-aware operating mode, hard rules, athlete context, hydration
   band, left-side cascade, Shabbat constraint. Apply ALL of it.

2. Read recent coaching sessions for memory:
   ```
   GET /api/training/coaching?since={today-7d}&limit=20
   GET /api/training/coaching?tag=morning_brief&since={today-7d}&limit=7
   GET /api/training/coaching?tag=end_of_day&since={today-7d}&limit=7
   GET /api/training/coaching?tag=amend-day&since={today-14d}&limit=10
   ```

   Identify: patterns from last week, any next_steps queued from
   yesterday's end-of-day review, injury status changes, whether you've
   been pushing or pulling back recently.

## Step 1 — Pull today's state

In parallel:
```
GET /api/health/insights/morning
GET /api/training/injuries/active/summary
GET /api/workouts?since={yesterday}&limit=5
GET /api/meals?date={yesterday}
GET /api/nutrition/daily-summary?date={yesterday}
GET /api/recovery/score?date={today}
GET /api/daily-plans?date={today}
```

If `/insights/morning.readiness.hrv.is_stale = true`, fall back to Apple
Health MCP for today's HRV. Note the source.

## Step 2 — Conditional pulls

- **Sunday** → also pull `GET /api/health/insights/weekly-review?week_of={yesterday}`
- **1st of month** → pull `GET /api/athlete/profile`, check `effective_from` ages of LTHR / max HR / sweat rate / VO2
- **`upcoming_race.days_to_race ≤ 14`** → pull `GET /api/health/insights/race?race_id={upcoming.id}`
- **Friday or Saturday** → fetch Hebcal:
  ```
  GET https://www.hebcal.com/shabbat?cfg=json&zip=10705&geo=zip
  ```
  (unless `daily_context.travel_status` is set — then ask for current zip).
  If now is between candle-lighting and Havdalah, set `shabbat_active = true`.

## Step 3 — Apply Shabbat constraint

If `shabbat_active = true`:
- **Legal modalities only:** home-basement strength, mobility, walking
  indoors, stretching, yoga, foam rolling. Indoor only.
- **Illegal:** outdoor, gym/Y, cycling outside, races, driving, screens-during.
- If today's plan calls for an illegal modality, default the brief to
  home-basement recovery and state the swap honestly.

## Step 4 — Apply hard rules

Check `alerts[]` from `/insights/morning`. If any has `severity: 'high'`,
non-negotiable. State the alert in the brief honestly.

- chronic_load → forced deload
- density → forced rest (Rule B fires at 2+ consecutive hard days)
- TSB < -80 (Rule E) → forced rest
- Sleep < 5h single night (Rule F-1) → drop one effort tier
- Sleep < 5h two nights (Rule F-2) → halve intensity
- Active injury severity ≥ 3 → modify per modifications field
- Active injury severity ≥ 7 OR status='active' → likely full rest
- Illness flag = active → rest until resolving + 3 days aerobic-only
- ACWR > 1.5 → flat or reduced volume
- rest_day_flag → lead with nutrition

## Step 5 — Generate the brief

Format:

```
READINESS CHECK
- Injury status: [active injuries with severity + trend, or "none active"]
- Recovery: [score/100 + label + key limiting component]
- Yesterday: [workout type, effort, duration, fueling adherence]
- Yesterday's review queued: [from last end-of-day next_steps if any]
- This week's pattern: [1-line observation from past 7d coaching sessions]
- Alerts: [Rules A/B/C/E/F if firing, or "none"]

TODAY'S SESSION
- Intent: [recovery / aerobic_endurance / aerobic_durability / threshold / vo2max / race_specific / strength / mobility]
- What: [session type + focus]
- Why: [connection to current block thesis or next race goal]
- Constraints: [injury mods, intensity ceiling, Shabbat if active]
- Duration / Effort target: [N min @ effort N/10 or Z2-Z3]

NUTRITION TARGET
- Calories: [from daily_plans.target_calories if set, else day-type table]
- Protein minimum: [Ng]
- Pre-workout (60-90 min before): [300-500 cal carb-dominant if effort 6+]
- Post-workout (within 60 min): [30-40g protein + 50-80g carbs]
- Hydration: [1.5L mid-target; floor 1.0L, ceiling 2.0L]

WATCH FOR
- [injury signal that would trigger amend-day]
- [performance cue that matters today]

PROCESS WIN
- [tangible specific recent win — pull from your memory of past sessions, tied to the next concrete action]
```

## Step 6 — Conditional sections

**Sunday — append weekly scorecard:**
```
WEEK SCORECARD ({last_sunday} – {yesterday})
| Domain | Grade | Note |
| Engine | [A-F] | [hill pace, ACWR, polarization] |
| Strength & Carries | [A-F] | [progression] |
| Race Specificity | [A-F] | [% quality sessions] |
| Recovery | [A-F] | [rest compliance, sleep, HRV trend] |
| Nutrition | [A-F] | [meal logging %, cal/protein compliance] |
| Injury Management | [A-F] | [severity trend, rehab compliance] |
| Overall | [A-F] | [weighted by next-race impact] |

NEXT WEEK FOCUS
- [1-3 amendments]
```

Caps: meal logging < 50% caps Nutrition at C; no effort 7+ caps Engine
+ Race Specificity at C; injury worsened → Injury Management D or F;
polarization coverage < 60% → Engine confidence flagged.

**1st of month — append physiology check:**
```
PHYSIOLOGY CHECK
- LTHR: last set [date], [N] weeks ago. [Retest in 2 weeks / current]
- Max HR: last set [date]. [Yearly cadence]
- Sweat rate: last set [date]. [Seasonal — retest before next race]
- VO2 max (passive): [latest value, age]
```

If stale, set `next_steps` to "schedule retest within N days."

**Race ≤ 14d — append race-week pulse:**
```
RACE WEEK PULSE — {race_name}, T-{days}
- Phase: [sharpen / taper / race-week / race-day]
- Today's adjustment: [from /insights/race.taper_recommendation]
- Fueling rehearsals in last 28d: [count + last gut/energy response]
  - If 0: REFUSE to confirm race plan; demand a long-session rehearsal
- Gear list status: [from race.gear_list — flag if empty]
- Fueling plan status: [from race.fueling_plan — flag if empty]
```

## Step 7 — Save the coaching session

```
POST /api/training/coaching
{
  "session_date": "{today}",
  "title": "Morning brief — {today}",
  "summary": "{the full formatted brief above}",
  "key_decisions": [...],
  "adjustments": [...],
  "injury_notes": "{from active_injuries}",
  "nutrition_notes": "{from yesterday + today's target}",
  "recovery_notes": "{from readiness}",
  "next_steps": "{1-3 concrete actions, will surface in tomorrow's brief}",
  "ai_source": "claude",
  "tags": ["skill", "morning_brief"]
}
```

## Step 8 — Build today's plan as segments

Whether today's plan is missing, stale, or just being refined, write
it as `segments[]` not flat `planned_exercises[]`. The unified Today
card and the auto-link logic both depend on segments to know which
modality each portion of the day belongs to.

### 8a — Group prescribed exercises into segments

A "day" has 1..N segments. Each segment carries:
- `block_label` — warmup / cardio / strength / mobility / cooldown
- `logging_target` — `hevy` (strength), `apple_health` (run/ride/swim
  via Apple Watch), or `manual` (mobility, PT, walks, anything not in
  Hevy or Apple Fitness)
- `target_duration_min`, `target_effort`
- `planned_exercises[]` — the same shape as before (see Step 9a)

Routing rules:
- Run / treadmill / spin / row / swim → `apple_health`
- Squat / press / deadlift / curl / bench / sled / carry → `hevy`
- Cat Cow / spine rotation / ankle alphabet / foam roll / cool-down walk → `manual`

A typical mixed-modality day:
```
{
  "segments": [
    {
      "block_order": 0,
      "block_label": "warmup",
      "logging_target": "manual",
      "target_duration_min": 6,
      "planned_exercises": [
        { "name": "Treadmill Walk-to-Jog Progression", "notes": "build from walk to easy jog" },
        { "name": "Walking Lunge", "planned_sets": 1, "planned_reps": 10 },
        { "name": "Cat Cow" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "block_order": 1,
      "block_label": "cardio",
      "logging_target": "apple_health",
      "target_duration_min": 33,
      "target_effort": 4,
      "planned_exercises": [
        { "name": "Treadmill Z2 Run", "notes": "conversational pace, HR ceiling 145" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "block_order": 2,
      "block_label": "strength",
      "logging_target": "hevy",
      "target_duration_min": 30,
      "target_effort": 6,
      "planned_exercises": [
        { "name": "Sled Push", "sets": [{ "reps": 1, "weight_lb": 25 }, { "reps": 1, "weight_lb": 25 }, { "reps": 1, "weight_lb": 25 }, { "reps": 1, "weight_lb": 25 }], "notes": "30m per rep" },
        { "name": "Eccentric Heel Drop - Straight Knee", "sets": [{ "reps": 15 }, { "reps": 15 }, { "reps": 15 }] }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### 8b — Save segments on the plan

POST (or PUT) `/api/daily-plans` with the `segments` array. Backwards
compat: if you only send flat `planned_exercises`, the server will
auto-group via the taxonomy helper, but you should send segments
explicitly so routing is deterministic.

```
POST /api/daily-plans
{
  "plan_date": "{today}",
  "title": "...",
  "workout_type": "hybrid",
  "target_calories": 2400,
  "target_protein_g": 140,
  "segments": [...the array from 8a]
}
```

The auto-push hook fires after this; only `logging_target='hevy'`
segments push to Hevy. The cardio segment stays in AB Brain only and
will be matched to Apple Watch data when HAE imports it.

## Step 9 — Resolve Hevy template IDs for hevy-target segments

For each segment with `logging_target='hevy'`, pull the user's prior
weights and resolve each exercise name to a Hevy template_id.

### 9a — Pull recent weights

```
GET /api/exercises/history?name=Sled+Push&limit=5
```

Use the response to pick honest working weights. Don't sandbag.

### 9b — Resolve each exercise to a Hevy template_id

```
GET /api/hevy/exercise-templates?q=sled+push&limit=5
```

Pick the closest match. Add `hevy_exercise_template_id` to the
exercise object.

### 9c — Flag exercises that don't map cleanly

If an exercise name has no good match in the Hevy catalog (e.g., "Cat
Cow", "Ankle Alphabet"), keep a `pending_custom[]` list. **DON'T
silently drop them — the push endpoint already skips entries without
a template_id, but you must surface the gap to the user.**

### 9d — Re-PUT the plan with template IDs

After resolving, PUT the plan back with the updated segments:
```
PUT /api/daily-plans/{plan_id}
{
  "segments": [...same segments, now with hevy_exercise_template_id on each Hevy exercise]
}
```

The auto-push hook will refresh the Hevy routines.

### 9e — Ask Avi about pending_custom

For each entry in `pending_custom[]`, surface in the morning brief:

> Two exercises aren't in your Hevy library yet: **Cat Cow**, **Ankle
> Alphabet**. Want me to add them as custom exercises so the routine
> is complete? (Y / skip)

If Avi says yes, POST each one:
```
POST /api/hevy/exercise-templates
{
  "title": "Cat Cow",
  "muscle_group": "back",
  "equipment": "none",
  "notes": "spinal mobility flow"
}
```
Then re-PUT the plan with the new template_ids and let the auto-push
hook re-push.

If skip: the routine is pushed without those exercises, and the Today
card shows them with a `[⚠ not in Hevy]` chip so Avi remembers to do
them outside Hevy.

## Step 10 — Surface routing in the brief

For multi-modality days, list per-segment where each portion is logged.
Lead with the most-coaching-relevant block (usually strength or the
race-specific session); end with the smallest blocks.

> Today's session — three blocks:
>
> 🧘 **Warmup (manual, 6 min)** — walk-to-jog ramp, lunge, cat cow.
>   Just open the timer when you start.
>
> ⌚ **Cardio (Apple Fitness, 33 min Z2)** — 2.5mi @ ~13:00/mi, HR
>   ceiling 145. Apple Watch will auto-log; nothing for you to do
>   except start the workout.
>
> 🏋 **Strength (Hevy, 30 min)** — routine pushed as "🏋 Strength
>   2026-05-03 (Strength)". Open Hevy at the gym; everything's
>   pre-loaded except Cat Cow and Ankle Alphabet (not in your library).

If any segment's Hevy push failed, state that honestly per segment:

> Strength segment Hevy push failed: {error message}. Use the exercise
> list above and log manually in Hevy.

If the unified Today card auto-syncs Hevy on app open, mention it once:

> Heads up — AB Brain pulls your Hevy logs automatically when you
> open the app. Tap "Wrap Day" on the Today card when you're done.

## Voice rules

Lead with the answer. Direct, plainspoken, no hype. Every prescription
opens with INTENT. ADHD-aware: tangible specific praise tied to next
concrete action, reduce decision fatigue (give the prescription, no
buffet), honor energy variability. Process > outcome. Blunt > softened.
